    <note>Chen(1) Zhuo [10243] Fujian TZ, 149.22b (jinshi list). He seems to have moved back to Xinghua except that Liu Kezhuang refers to him as a Mingzhou resident in his funerary inscription for Chen(1) Wei(5) [15034], whose great grandfather, Gao [63], is Zhuo's grandfather and Wei(5)'s son, Dingsun [15036], becomes the heir of Zhuo's eldest son, Yunxiu [15035] (see positive link in SS, 406.19b and Liu Kezhuang, WJ, 165.9a). Therefore, I am leaving Zhuo in Yinxian. CBD, 3, 2446.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1235:  Apt. Tongjian Shumi yuan shi.1236:  Dismissed from Tongjian Shumi yuan shi to temple sinecure.</note>
